# Coding Standards

- Follow existing naming conventions in the module you are editing.
- Keep functions under 50 lines; extract helpers when logic grows.
- No commented-out code in commits.
- Docstrings on public modules and complex functions.
- Import order: stdlib → third-party → local.
- Constants in `shared/constants/` — no magic strings in business logic.
